LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE SENATE
SENATE BILL NO. 1154
BY FINANCE COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO THE APPROPRIATION TO THE COMMISSION ON THE ARTS; APPROPRIATING
3 ADDITIONAL MONEYS TO THE COMMISSION ON THE ARTS FOR FISCAL YEAR 2026;
4 PROVIDING FOR RESTRICTIONS RELATED TO FEDERAL FUNDS; PROVIDING FOR CON-
5 DITIONS, LIMITATIONS, AND RESTRICTIONS; AND DECLARING AN EMERGENCY AND
6 PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.
7 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
8 SECTION 1. In addition to any other appropriation provided by law,
9 there is hereby appropriated to the Commission on the Arts an additional
10 $18,400 from the General Fund to be expended for trustee and benefit payments
11 for the period July 1, 2025, through June 30, 2026.
12 SECTION 2. FEDERAL FUNDING RESTRICTIONS. Pursuant to Section
13 67-3511(2), Idaho Code, legislative appropriations shall not be transferred
14 from one fund to another fund unless expressly approved by the Legislature.
15 Appropriations made pursuant to this act contingent on anticipated federal
16 funding, grants, or programs shall not be supplanted by state funds in the
17 event of any reduction or elimination of such federal support without Leg-
18 islative approval. The agency receiving the appropriation shall take all
19 necessary actions to ensure that the state is not obligated to replace lost
20 federal funds. Pursuant to Section 67-1917, Idaho Code, the agency will
21 submit an inventory of federal funds utilized by the agency. State funds ap-
22 propriated to satisfy match requirements for federal funds shall be reverted
23 to the maximum extent possible if federal funds requiring match are reduced
24 or eliminated. The agency shall promptly notify the Budget and Policy Anal-
25 ysis Division of the Legislative Services Office of any significant changes
26 related to federal funding, grants, or programs. This does not apply to
27 standard federal funding adjustments that take place within an agency's cost
28 allocation plan or indirect expenditure plan for indirect costs and agency
29 support staff, FMAP adjustments, or entitlement programs.
30 SECTION 3. CONDITIONS, LIMITATIONS, AND RESTRICTIONS. Appropriations
31 made pursuant to this act are subject to the conditions, limitations, and re-
32 strictions specified in this act.
33 SECTION 4. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
34 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after
35 July 1, 2025.

